    "recap_headline": "University of Richmond Athletics",
    "recap_text": "RICHMOND, Va. \u2013\nThe University of Richmond baseball team dropped a 5-1 decision to Saint Joseph's Hawks Sunday at Pitt Field in the series finale in Atlantic 10 Conference action.\nRichmond, now 10-10 on the year and 0-3 in league action, closes out a 12-game home stand Tuesday hosting Big Ten foe Maryland at Pitt Field. First pitch is set for 2 p.m. and will be streamed on ESPN+.\nSaint Joseph's, 8-9 on the season and 3-0 in conference action, scored in the first inning on a sacrifice fly, connecting a walk and a double. The Hawks added two more runs in the third on a two-run double, taking advantage of a base hit and a Spider miscue.\nAngel Santiago-Cruz\n(1-1) took the loss, making it into the third inning for the Spiders. Santiago-Cruz allowed three runs, one earned, on two hits, a walk, a hit batter and two strikeouts in two and a third of an inning of work.\nIn the bottom of the third,\nDylan Winebrenner\ndrew a walk before taking third on\nMichael Elko\ndoubled down the right field line.\nRyan Recio\npushed in Winebrenner with a sacrifice fly to center for the Spiders only run of the game.\nRichmond had two runners reach in the fifth, but the Spiders were stopped with a double play. With two outs in the sixth,\nChris Schaller\ndrew a nine-pitch walk before he raced around the bases on\nAidan O'Keefe's\ndouble to deep left field. Schaller was called out at the home as the Hawks catcher moved into the running lane and blocked the plate.\nChayse Gruber\ntossed four full innings, scattering four hits, one home run in the seventh, one hit batter and four strikeouts.\nElko led off the eighth inning with a base hit to left then advanced to third on two wild pitches.\nGrant Kennedy\ndrew a two-out walk but both runners were stranded.\nFreshman\nAaron Van Tuyle\ntossed a scoreless inning and two-thirds, allowing one hit.\nDom Ruggiero\ntossed the ninth, allowing one run on one hit and striking out two."
